ls — list directory contents

SYNOPSIS
  ls [-l] [-a] [PATH...]

DESCRIPTION
  Lists names of entries in PATH. With no arguments, lists the current
  working directory. Paths in OCOS are absolute (starting with `/`) or
  resolved relative to PWD.

OPTIONS
  -l   long format: size, last-modified, type
  -a   include dotfiles

EXAMPLES
  ls /              entries in the root
  ls -l /etc        long listing of system config
  ls -a /home/root  include dotfiles in root's home

SEE ALSO
  cat(1), find(1), mounts(1)
